        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "Based on the SRD-46 amino-acid pKa shortlist, the best candidate is **penicillamine** (`ligand_5857`).\n\n| Ligand | SRD-46 ID | Key donor(s) at pH 7 | Relevant pKa data from SRD-46 | Expected Cu²⁺/Ni²⁺ selectivity at pH 7 |\n|---|---:|---|---|---|\n| Penicillamine | ligand_5857 | COO⁻, NH₂/NH₃⁺, **thiol/thiolate** | −1.9, **7.96**, 10.67 | **Highest** |\n| 5-Amino-3-thiapentanoic acid | ligand_5875 | COO⁻, amine, thioether S | 3.18, 9.53 | High, but likely below penicillamine |\n| 6-Amino-3-thiahexanoic acid | ligand_5876 | COO⁻, amine, thioether S | 3.35, 10.19 | High-moderate |\n| 6-Amino-4-thiahexanoic acid | ligand_5877 | COO⁻, amine, thioether S | 9.54 listed | High-moderate |\n| 4-Imidazolylacetic acid | ligand_5964 | COO⁻, imidazole N | 3.1, 7.26 | Moderate |\n| 3-(4-Imidazolyl)propanoic acid | ligand_5965 | COO⁻, imidazole N | 3.83, 7.44 | Moderate |\n| 2-Hydroxy-3-(4-imidazolyl)propanoic acid | ligand_5966 | COO⁻, imidazole N, OH | 3.0, 7.31 | Moderate |\n\n\n**Penicillamine would give the best Cu²⁺ vs Ni²⁺ selectivity at pH 7** among the amino-acid-type ligands surfaced from SRD-46.\n\nWhy it stands out:\n\n| Factor | Penicillamine consequence |\n|---|---|\n| Soft donor present | Sulfur donor strongly favors Cu²⁺ over Ni²⁺ |\n| pKa near neutral pH | Thiol-related step at **pKa 7.96** means Cu²⁺ can promote thiolate binding around pH 7 |\n| Amino-acid scaffold | Still provides the usual carboxylate/amine framework for chelation |\n\nIn contrast, ordinary amino acids like glycine or β-alanine mostly offer only hard/borderline **O,N** donors, so they are not expected to discriminate strongly between Cu²⁺ and Ni²⁺.",
